===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ine-pro|la}} {{recons|bʰleh₃-||flower, blossom|lang=ine-pro}}, from {{recons|bʰel-||to bloom|lang=ine-pro}}.  Cognates include Ancient Greek {{term|φύλλον|tr=phullon|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, Gothic {{term|sc=Goth|𐌱𐌻𐍉𐌼𐌰|tr=blōma|lang=got}} and Old English {{term|blostm|blōstm|lang=ang}}, {{term|blæd||leaf|lang=ang}} (English {{term|blossom|lang=en}}, {{term|blade|lang=en}}).

